Class SevenZipNativeInitializationException

java.lang.Object

          net.sf.sevenzipjbinding.SevenZipNativeInitializationException
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class SevenZipNativeInitializationException
extends java.lang.Exception

SevenZip initialization exception. This exception can be thrown by any of initialization routines indicating problems with loading native SevenZipJBinding library into JVM.

Since:
4.65-1
Author:
Boris Brodski

SevenZipNativeInitializationException

public SevenZipNativeInitializationException(java.lang.Throwable cause)
Constructs a new exception with the specified cause and a detail message of (cause==null ? null : cause.toString()) (which typically contains the class and detail message of cause). This constructor is useful for exceptions that are little more than wrappers for other throwables (for example, PrivilegedActionException).
